<exercise checkit-seed="0022" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>P= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
3 &amp; 7 &amp; 4 &amp; 1 \\
-1 &amp; 2 &amp; -2 &amp; 6 \\
-1 &amp; -4 &amp; -1 &amp; -3 \\
-2 &amp; 6 &amp; -1 &amp; 6
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>P^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
30 &amp; 29 &amp; 64 &amp; -2 \\
21 &amp; 20 &amp; 45 &amp; -1 \\
-54 &amp; -52 &amp; -116 &amp; 3 \\
-20 &amp; -19 &amp; -43 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

